title: Google\Cloud\Video\Stitcher\V1\LiveSession
name: LiveSession
description:
Metadata for a live session.

Generated from protobuf message google.cloud.video.stitcher.v1.LiveSession

Extends Google\Protobuf\Internal\Message

methods.name: __construct
methods.description: Constructor.

params.name: data
params.description: Optional. Data for populating the Message object.

params.name: data.name
params.description: Output only. The name of the live session, in the form of projects/{project}/locations/{location}/liveSessions/{id}.

params.name: data.play_uri
params.description: Output only. The URI to play the live session's ad-stitched stream.

params.name: data.source_uri
params.description: The URI of the live session's source stream.

params.name: data.default_ad_tag_id
params.description: The default ad tag to use when no ad tag ids are specified in an ad break's SCTE-35 message. default_ad_tag_id is necessary when adTagMap has more than one key. Its value must be present in the adTagMap.

params.name: data.ad_tag_map
params.description: Key value pairs for ad tags. Ads parsed from ad tags must be MP4 videos each with at least one audio track.

params.name: data.ad_tag_macros
params.description: Key value pairs for ad tag macro replacement. If the specified ad tag URI has macros, this field provides the mapping to the value that will replace the macro in the ad tag URI. Macros are designated by square brackets. For example: Ad tag URI: "https://doubleclick.google.com/ad/1?geo_id=[geoId]" Ad tag macros: {"geoId": "123"} Fully qualified ad tag: "https://doubleclick.google.com/ad/1?geo_id=123"

params.name: data.client_ad_tracking
params.description: Whether client side ad tracking is enabled. If enabled, the client player is expected to trigger playback and activity events itself. Otherwise, server side ad tracking is enabled and the Video Stitcher API will trigger playback events on behalf of the client player.

params.name: data.default_slate_id
params.description: The default slate to use when no slates are specified in an ad break's SCTE-35 message. When specified, this value must match the ID for a slate that has already been created via the CreateSlate method.

params.name: data.stitching_policy
params.description: Defines the stitcher behavior in case an ad does not align exactly with the ad break boundaries. If not specified, the default is COMPLETE_AD.

params.name: data.manifest_options
params.description: Additional options that affect the output of the manifest.

params.name: data.stream_id
params.description: Output only. The generated ID of the LiveSession's source stream.
